## Default Definition of Done (DoD) for User Story Development

A user story is **done** when it meets all these criteria:

### Code Quality

- [ ] **Code complete** - All acceptance criteria implemented
- [ ] **Code reviewed** - Peer review approved
- [ ] **Coding standards followed** - Consistent with team conventions
- [ ] **No known defects** - No critical/major bugs remaining

### Testing

- [ ] **Unit tests written** - Adequate coverage for new code
- [ ] **Unit tests passing** - All tests green
- [ ] **Integration tests passing** (if applicable)
- [ ] **QA tested** - Tested by QA or team member other than developer
- [ ] **Acceptance criteria verified** - All conditions met

### Technical

- [ ] **Builds successfully** - No build errors in CI/CD pipeline
- [ ] **Merged to main branch** - Code integrated to development/main
- [ ] **No regressions** - Existing functionality unaffected
- [ ] **Performance acceptable** - No significant performance degradation

### Documentation

- [ ] **Code documented** - Comments/docstrings where needed
- [ ] **Technical documentation updated** (if applicable)
- [ ] **User documentation updated** (if applicable)

### Deployment

- [ ] **Deployed to staging/test environment**
- [ ] **Ready for production deployment**
